OREON Pump Maintenance Manual

Scope: centrifugal and hydraulic pumps serving cooling water and hydraulic circuits.

Normal operating envelope: stable suction pressure above 2.5 bar, discharge pressure within design
range, vibration below 4.5 mm/s RMS, bearing temperature below 80 C, and no visible seal leakage.

Pump cavitation indicators include low suction pressure, rattling or gravel-like sound, fluctuating
discharge pressure, elevated vibration, mechanical seal wear, and impeller pitting. Response:
inspect suction strainer, open suction valve fully, remove air ingress, validate NPSH margin, reduce
speed temporarily, and inspect impeller and seal faces.

Seal failure indicators include leakage rate growth, abrasive water contamination, shaft sleeve
scoring, overheating, and pressure spikes. Replace seal faces, inspect sleeve, and flush circuit.
